by wachterjohannes at 2026-05-15T19:30:58Z

Good point — instead of a symlink I went with a different approach that achieves the same goal:

- `AGENTS.md` is now the canonical, general AI-agent guidance file (carries the design principles + all the component docs).
- `CLAUDE.md` is reduced to an `@AGENTS.md` Claude Code import plus a small Claude Code-specific section.

That way the shared content lives in one place and the two files can't drift, while CLAUDE.md can still carry anything that's specifically Claude Code-related.
